snippet: The Times spoke to Mr. Richmond, a Louisiana congressman and former chair of the Congressional Black Caucus, about his role with the campaign and the 1994 crime bill.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidential campaign is naming Representative Cedric Richmond to a major leadership role within the organization, a move that could bolster Mr. Biden’s standing with some congressional Democrats and African-American leaders in politically important states, even as the former vice president faces scrutiny over his record on criminal justice issues.
abstract: The Times spoke to Mr. Richmond, a Louisiana congressman and former chair of the Congressional Black Caucus, about his role with the campaign and the 1994 crime bill.

snippet: The president plans to impose a 5 percent tariff on all imported goods from Mexico, a tax that would “gradually increase” until the flow of immigrants across the border stopped.
lead_paragraph: Good Friday morning. Here are some of the stories making news in Washington and politics today.
abstract: The president plans to impose a 5 percent tariff on all imported goods from Mexico, a tax that would “gradually increase” until the flow of immigrants across the border stopped.
headline_main: On Politics: Trump to Hit Mexico With Tariffs

snippet: Joe Biden’s campaign is challenging the political muscle of the Democratic Party’s left wing, which is desperate for a nominee who embraces its policy goals.
lead_paragraph: Optimism filled the Prospect Park air as more than 100 supporters of Senator Elizabeth Warren’s presidential campaign gathered last week for an organizing event called “How to Be All In for Elizabeth.” But as dusk approached, the final “She Has a Plan” button was handed out, and the crowd of mostly millennial Brooklynites began to disperse, hope gave way to skepticism.
abstract: Joe Biden’s campaign is challenging the political muscle of the Democratic Party’s left wing, which is desperate for a nominee who embraces its policy goals.

headline_main: The 2020 Race Is Testing Progressives’ Power. They’re Pushing Back.
headline_print_headline: Biden’s Appeal to Political Center  Tests Power of Democrats’ Left Wing

snippet: The Democratic front-runner helped make the country a lot safer.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden has been attacked by politicians on the left — and now, thanks to Donald Trump, on the right — for his role in shepherding the 1994 crime bill through Congress. One of these attacks is simply cynical. The other is dangerous.
